    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="PT">(A) Status of national GHG inventories ;
(B) Status of assessment National Circumstances  and vulnerability and adaptation measures;
(C) Biennial Update Report (BUR) for reference year 2012 and 2014;
(D) Level of institutional capacity in Brazil for education, training and public awareness related to climate change.
(E)  Publication of  Fourth National Communication (FNC);</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2016">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="PT">A) TNC GHG inventory available for period 1990-1994 (INC), 1990-2000 (SNC) and 1990-2010 (TNC);
B) TNC includes assessment of National circumstances until 2013;
C) First BUR;
D) Fragmented initiatives on education, training and public awareness;
E) TNC published in April 2016.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="PT">1.	GHG inventory available for period 2011- 2016;
2.	Report on National Circumstances and description of steps taken or envisaged for the Convention implementation regarding the period 2014 to 2017;
3.	4th National Communication fully prepared and published;
4.	At least one research group supporting education, training and public awareness initiatives
5.	BUR3 published in 2019.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="PT">1.	GHG inventory available for period 2011- 2016, data from LULUCF, Energy, Waste and Agriculture Sectors is nearly 50% completed. 
2.	TNC includes updated assessment of National circumstances, as well as measures on vulnerability and adaptation. Consultants hired and studies underway for updating of information. 12 products were validated by mid-2019.
3.	Not applicable at this moment;
4.	The project has been successfully developing publications and information content to assist in the process of raising awareness about climate change (translation of one Special Report from IPCC and designing of 10 informative infographics), besides holding meetings with counterparts.
5.	BUR 3 was presented to UNFCCC in March 2019.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="PT">Targets by the end of the project:
1.	National GHG inventory for the sectors: (i) energy; (ii) industry; (iii) agriculture; (iv) LULUCF; and (v) waste for 2011-2014 produced; and time-series 1990-2010 refined;
2.	Report on National Circumstances and description of steps taken or envisaged for the Convention implementation regarding the period 2014 to 2017;
3.	4th National Communication fully prepared and published;
4.	At least one research group supporting education, training and public awareness initiatives related to climate change;
5.	Biennial Update Report (BUR) 2 and 3 submitted ;</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="PT">1.	National GHG inventory for the period from 1990 to 2016 under progress (technical team hired, as well as technical workshops conducted by June 2020);
2.	In the period from Jun/2019 to Jul/2020, the relevant reports to this activity went through a process of public consultation with specialists. In addition, the subsidies developed for this component were shared through a joint meeting with the government and later made available for analysis. They are currently being consolidated as four chapters in the document of the Fourth National Communication (4NC), which will be revised and validated by the government;
3.	In 2020, a company was hired to develop graphic elements that will be part of the publication of the Fourth National Communication.
4.	The project has been successfully developing publications and information content to assist in the process of raising awareness about climate change: including 10 thematic infographics; factsheets and dashboards; and translation and dissemination of two Special Reports from IPCC;
5.	The initial objective for this component of the project was successfully completed, with the submission of BUR2 and BUR3 to the UNFCCC. BUR4 under development.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="PT">Targets by the end of the project:
1.	National GHG inventory for the sectors: (i) energy; (ii) industry; (iii) agriculture; (iv) LULUCF; and (v) waste for 2011-2014 produced; and time-series 1990-2010 refined;
2.	Report on National Circumstances and description of steps taken or envisaged for the Convention implementation regarding the period 2014 to 2017;
3.	4th National Communication fully prepared and published;
4.	At least one research group supporting education, training and public awareness initiatives related to climate change;
5.	Biennial Update Report (BUR) 2 and 3 submitted ;</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="PT">1.	The GHG inventory for the period 1990-2016 was completed, reviewed by experts, and validated by the Government of Brazil in 2020. The inventory covers the following sectors/sources: (i) energy; (ii) industrial processes and product use (IPPU); (iii) agriculture; (iv) LULUCF; and, (v) waste. The data series covers to additional years (2015-2016) to those originally planned for (1990-2014);
2.	The assessment of national circumstances was completed, reviewed by experts, and validated by the Government of Brazil in 2019 and 2020. The information produced was compiled and included in chapters 1, 4 and 5 of 4NC.42;
3.	Brazil submitted the 4NC to the UNFCCC secretariat on 31 December 2020. The document is available on the UNFCCC website under https://unfccc.int/documents/267657;
4.	The project developed and implemented a communication plan to disseminate the results from the elaboration of 4NC. As part of the plan, the project prepared educational materials and held regional events to raise awareness. An informal group with representatives from MCTI and partner universities was established in 2021. In the context of this informal group, the project has commissioned the elaboration of education products, including materials for teachers and school children (e.g. books, games, etc.);
5.	Brazil submitted the second BUR (BUR 2) on 3 March 2017 and the third BUR (BUR 3)on 22 July 2020. Moreover, with support from the project, Brazil also submitted the fourth BUR (BUR 4)on 31 December 2020. The reports are available on the UNFCCC website under: BUR 2 https://unfccc.int/documents/180612, BUR 3 https://unfccc.int/documents/193513, BUR 4 &lt;https://unfccc.int/documents/267661&gt;</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
